Media personality Minnie Dlamini-Jones says the lockdown has exposed the truth about showbiz. This after several of her industry colleagues have complained about being financially affected by the lockdown, as they were unable to work. In a tweet, the star pointed out some of the drawbacks of showbiz such as overhyped PR stunts while those in it are undervalued and underpaid. Tweeted Minnie: "This lockdown is truly exposing the entertainment industry for what it is. Underpaid, undervalued and over hyped PR stunts!!! Things aren't what they seem... We need to do better as a whole. Clout doesn't pay the bills". Meanwhile, the likes of Stoan Seate have also complained about the Department of Arts and Culture's budget of R150 million, saying it isn't enough. 